I teach Piano, Ukulele and Guitar from beginner to intermediate, young children to adults. I have taught private music lessons since 2013. Prior to teaching lessons, I worked in early childhood education and also have co-run a music / art summer camp.\
\
My teaching is based on a foundation in music theory, technique and history. I use several different books and methods in addition to always incorporating new material. I teach from a classical foundation but equally draw upon folk, blues and popular music, as I believe it\'92s important to expose my students to different methods, styles, and genres. This could mean working on a classical piece, drawing upon the song cannon, or incorporating the voice with playing. Eventually we might dabble in songwriting or improvisation if the student has any interest.\
\
I also teach songwriting and improvisation specifically for the student that wants to focus on one of those.\
